6:
Holy... I don't think I've ever held this
much money in my life!
9:
Hehe... Now to think about how to
spend it all!
13:
Frittering away all your money
might lead to problems, you know.
Why not try putting some money
away to grow your savings?
16:
Savings? Hehe, you sound just like
my grandpa.
21:
G-grandpa? Young people care
about budgeting as well!
26:
Whaaatever! Today I wanna go...
here!
31:
Tada!

A special issue of the Oculus—with a
full-color front page too!
35:
A special report on cafés in
Palpebra?
39:
Exactly!

And I'm like, totally going to try out
this limited time only Tapioca
Meteor Tea!
42: What kind of a name is that?
46:
A super delish-sounding one! You
can even add these special
Heavenly Toppings on, oh my gosh!
52:
Sickly Sweet Syrup? I'll be passing on
that, if you don't mind.
58:
Gotta watch your blood sugar levels,
right Grandpa? Hehe. Alk, Stella, let's
ditch Light and go ourselves!
67:
This Tapioca Meteor Tea was
delicious.
72:
Told you so! Getting the extra
toppings was also totally the right
call.
77:
I... I think I'm getting heartburn.

Can we go back now?
81:
Huh? What are you talking about?
We've still got SHOPPING to do!
86: Let's get a move on, you two!
91:
Oh my gosh, Palpebra is like, even
better than I imagined!
97:
That last store we went to was
amazing! So many cute outfits. Oh,
and they all looked SUPER cute on
you, Stella!
102:
I guess... Say, didn't they have cafés
and clothing stores back in your
hometown, Samantha?
107:
Uh, NO! Nowhere to buy food
either—you only ate what you were
able to get yourself!
110:
I was eating nothing but ILMS! Boiled
ilms, mashed ilms, ilm stew! And the
occasional bit of crag meat, when
we could catch some.
115:
Oh, sorry, did it again. Potatoes, I
mean. And crag is like... a wild pig
we have near our village.
119:
You know, I can actually kind of
empathize with that.
124:
But like, I guess it wasn't ALL bad. Life
in Shaman's Rest was probably
better than what most people have
to go through...
128:
But in Palpebra, you can get MONEY!
And money can be exchanged for
MANY potatoes!
130:
Plus, Palpebra has TAPIOCA bubble
tea! Praying to my ancestors never
got me any bubble tea!
132:
Somehow I don't think that's your
ancestors' fault...
136:
But like, nights were pretty, I guess.
Back home.
140:
I liked gazing at the stars at night.

But, that's like literally it.
144:
Perhaps we should go look at the
stars here in Palpebra too.
148:
Yeah, let's do that. I know a good
spot over there!
155:
Ohmygooooosh! The stars look so
different from over here!
158:
Palpebra's night sky is like... totally
beautiful too...
162:
When I look at the sky like this I
always feel like I'm so... small, you
know? That all my worries are just a
drop in the ocean.
171:
Well, duh! Everyone's got worries!

I guess I'm like, worried about the
future.
176:
You don't plan on being an
adventurer forever, I take it?
179:
I mean, I'm like, totally not cut out for
it. I really want to be a fashion
designer, but I don't know if that's
realistic either...
183:
Oh well. I like to think that one way or
another things will work out in the
end!
188:
For now, I'm happy to just sit here
and watch the stars with my friends.
It's nice.
201: Are you like, making fun of me?
206:
No, absolutely not! I just thought
that... we could all learn something
from you.
209: Huh? Well, whatever, if you say so!
214:
Gosh... I'll never get over how pretty
the stars are!
